SIMPLE: eternize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eternize
<hw>E*ter"nize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Eternized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Eterniziing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧terniser</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make eternal or
endless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This other [gift] served but to <qex>eternize</qex> woe.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make forever famous; to immortalize; <as>as, to
<ex>eternize</ex> one's self, a name, exploits</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>St. Alban's battle won by famous York,⟦br⟧
Shall be <qex>eternized</qex> in all age to come.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Etesian</ent>⟦br⟧
